14/02/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The money laundering trial involving members of alleged drug trafficker Darko Saric's group opens on Monday (February 14th) in Belgrade. Prosecutors say the group invested 20m euros in hotels and farms using money raised by selling cocaine. Saric, who is suspected of smuggling 2.5 tonnes of cocaine from South America, will be tried in absentia. Among those charged are lawyers and businessmen. (Tanjug, Blic, B92 - 14/02/11)
